    Computes the squared absolute value of a single-precision complex floating-
    point number.

    The absolute value of a complex number is its distance from zero.

    Parameters
    ----------
    z: Complex64
        Complex number.

    Returns
    -------
    y: number
        Squared absolute value.

    Examples
    --------
    > var y = {{alias}}( new {{alias:@stdlib/complex/float32/ctor}}( 5.0, 3.0 ) )
